<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880328-0146 </DOCNO><HL> Letters to the Editor: Trim Congress's Perks </HL><SO> </SO><G> CNG </G><TEXT>   Re Fed Chairman Alan Greenspan's testimony before the Senate Budget Committee (news article, March 3): I am one of the elderly people whose entitlement programs he would cut. I would be more than happy to have my entitlement programs cut if first Congress would cut its own entitlement programs, such as raises through the back door, junket trips for pleasure, pork barrels and some of the many other perks it enjoys.    Allan C. Bock   Sun City West, Ariz. </TEXT></DOC>